  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "For a long time after the war, when I went somewhere or drove somewhere, and there was a factory-- an innocent factory-- with the fire coming out the chimney, I always remember that first moment in Auschwitz and the stink-- cannot call it smell-- stink as if hair was burning or flesh was burning, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the shouting.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was a madhouse.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the zebras, I don't-- the zebras.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It-- it was-- I'm sure everybody was in shock.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I'm sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this German standing there, with his riding crop-- it must have been Mengele.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We didn't know-- and dividing people, just like when the Jewish transports arrived-- same thing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "For all I know, the train might have been a whole Jewish train with one additional, you know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Like Eichmann said, if you ever read the Eichmann's reports, he would say, I'm sending so many cars of Jews and attached is another car of gypsies, or and attached is another car-- he never said political prisoners-- vagabonds, or [NON-ENGLISH]-- what's the word in English-- anyhow, professional no-goodniks, you know.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
